Frost version 0.70
==================

Feasible Referential Object STorage

Frost is an extension of Moose providing persistence even to circular
structures like trees or loops.

See the individual module documentation for more information

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

	BerkeleyDB
	Carp
	Class::MOP
	Data::Dumper
	Data::UUID
	Exporter
	Fcntl
	File::Path
	IO::File
	Log::Log4perl
	Moose
	Scalar::Util
	Storable
	Tie::Cache::LRU
	Time::HiRes

For testing these modules are needed:

	DateTime::Format::MySQL
	List::Util
	List::MoreUtils
	Test::Deep
	Test::Differences
	Test::Exception
	Test::More
	Test::Requires

Optional modules to run some tests:

	Devel::Size
	Sys::MemInfo
	Declare::Constraints::Simple
	Regexp::Common
	Locale::US

Please see Makefile.PL for required versions.

